text: Ti mutasion ket mangnaynayon ti genetiko a kinanadumaduma, ken ti panagpili ket mangik-ikkat kadagitoy iti pagpilyan.
translated_text:
Ilocano: Ti Turkey ket napalawlawan ti baybay iti tallo nga igidna: Ti BayBay Aegean idiay laud, ti Nangisit a Baybay idiay amianan, ken ti Baybay Mediteranio idiay abagatan. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ilocano: Idi rugrugi ti giyera napanda idiay ngato iti baybay, ngem idi mabuo ti radar ken agbalbalinen a husto dagiti sabmarin ket napuersa a mapan iti uneg ti danum tapno saanda a makita. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Ilocano: Ti mutasion ket mangnaynayon ti genetiko a kinanadumaduma, ken ti panagpili ket mangik-ikkat kadagitoy iti pagpilyan. 
English: The submarines were very powerful and could penetrate the enemy's defenses.

English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ilocano: Idi rugrugi ti giyera napanda idiay ngato iti baybay, ngem idi mabuo ti radar ken agbalbalinen a husto dagiti sabmarin ket napuersa a mapan iti uneg ti danum tapno saanda a makita. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Ilocano: Agtapaw ti asero a dagum iti rabaw ti danum gapu iti surface tension. 
English: The submarines were very slow and had to travel at a very low speed to avoid being seen.

text: Awan ti makita malaksid ti klaro, napintas a tangatang iti ngato ken ii adu nga aglawlaw a banbantay. Bassit kadaytgitoy a lubong iti makita wenno mangngeg iti uneg ti kueba.
translated_text:
Ilocano: Ti Turkey ket napalawlawan ti baybay iti tallo nga igidna: Ti BayBay Aegean idiay laud, ti Nangisit a Baybay idiay amianan, ken ti Baybay Mediteranio idiay abagatan. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ilocano: Idi rugrugi ti giyera napanda idiay ngato iti baybay, ngem idi mabuo ti radar ken agbalbalinen a husto dagiti sabmarin ket napuersa a mapan iti uneg ti danum tapno saanda a makita. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Ilocano: Awan ti makita malaksid ti klaro, napintas a tangatang iti ngato ken ii adu nga aglawlaw a banbantay. Bassit kadaytgitoy a lubong iti makita wenno mangngeg iti uneg ti kueba. 
English: The submarines were very powerful, but they were also very vulnerable to the artillery fire of the enemy.
